  <prefix>Chapter</prefix>
  <num>01</num>
  <heading>The Blind</heading>
  <section>
    <prefix>Regulation</prefix>
    <num>.01</num>
    <heading>Receiving Exemption.</heading>
    <para>
      <num>A.</num>
      <text>The property of a blind person, held with the spouse as tenants by the entireties, is entitled to exemption.</text>
    </para>
    <para>
      <num>B.</num>
      <text>In tenancy in common and joint tenancy, the exemption is applied only to the undivided interest of the joint tenant or tenant in common, not against the total assessed valuation.</text>
    </para>
  </section>
